				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Soloing fear<a name="20402"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 04 9:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've read all the posts I could find on soloing here.  I would like to go here in the next couple of weeks alone if my guild does not plan a raid here.  I will be level 63 with FM.  The map I plan on using and where to AE kite is from here http://www.notacult.com/rancar/bardsoloepic.html
<br />
A few questions though.  
<br />

<br />
1- Should I invis in and run to NW corner by flaming wall and work my way back to the ZI, or start killing at ZI and work my way up.  I've read both options.  I am not sure I will want to pull from temple because I hate casters.
<br />

<br />
2- Never been to Fear before.  It seems there is a huge respawn on things here?  Like I get one shot to kill stuff then dont come back till next week?  Supposidly there is a guild on my server that raids fear every friday night, so would Sat morning be a good time for me to go, or will things have respawned by then.  Should I just go friday night instead?  If I could get in after a raid has taken down some of the baddies it would likely be better for me.
<br />

<br />
3- Not sure I understand the death touch thing.  The DT'ing mob gets upset when you outrun another mob?  Does this DT'ing mob have to literally touch you, or does it just do this from somewhere across the zone?
<br />

<br />
4- Any advice on how to loot bodies?  When I Ae a lot of times the last few mobs will be about 15% difference... and if I get additional adds after I start I will have to kill them as well.  Can I run them a bit away and AE snare them, and run back and loot?  7 minute corpse timers are not fun sometimes.
<br />

<br />
I know I'm probably crazy, but I'm tired of waiting around to get help with this.  As I'm sure a lot of us has experienced sometimes it's easier to just do things your way rather then having to change for others in group.  (like ever have a mage want to join in when your kiting, and their pet or they get agro and they die?) I've been AE kiting the dog camp in PON without dying (usually 11 of them)  So long as I have something like a tree to run around to keep as a point of reference I am OK.  And I will have a thurgadin gate potion to get out, and probably a back up regular gate potion as well.
<br />

<br />
Can a 63 do this, or do I get songs at 64 and 65 that would make me want to wait.</span></td>
